@url = http://localhost:5000
@roomUrl = {{url}}/api/rooms

### 1. GET all rooms
GET {{roomUrl}}

### ---------------------------------------------------
### FILTER BY STATUS
### ---------------------------------------------------

### 2. Filter - Available rooms
GET {{roomUrl}}?status=Available

### 3. Filter - Occupied rooms
GET {{roomUrl}}?status=Occupied

### 4. Filter - Maintenance rooms
GET {{roomUrl}}?status=Maintenance

### ---------------------------------------------------
### FILTER BY TYPE
### Note: Filtering by ID (1, 2...) is more standard for backend than by name
### Mapping: 1=Single, 2=Double, 3=Deluxe, 4=Luxury
### ---------------------------------------------------

### 5. Filter - Single Room (Type ID = 1)
GET {{roomUrl}}?type=1

### 6. Filter - Double Room (Type ID = 2)
GET {{roomUrl}}?type=2

### 7. Filter - Standard Room (Type ID = 3)
GET {{roomUrl}}?type=3

### 8. Filter - Luxury Room (Type ID = 4)
GET {{roomUrl}}?type=4

### ---------------------------------------------------
### COMBINE FILTERS
### ---------------------------------------------------

### 9. Available AND Single Room (ID 1)
GET {{roomUrl}}?status=Available&type=1

### 10. Available AND Double Room (ID 2)
GET {{roomUrl}}?status=Available&type=2

### 11. Occupied AND Standard Room (ID 3)
GET {{roomUrl}}?status=Occupied&type=3

### 12. Maintenance AND Single Room (ID 1)
GET {{roomUrl}}?status=Maintenance&type=1

### ---------------------------------------------------
### TEST EDGE CASES
### ---------------------------------------------------

### 13. Test invalid status (Should return an empty list [])
GET {{roomUrl}}?status=InvalidStatusName

### 14. Test missing parameters (Should return all rooms by default)
GET {{roomUrl}}

